        @Modifying
@Query(value="INSERT INTO currency_conversion (CCN_DATE, CCN_CUR_ID_FROM, CCN_CUR_ID_TO, CCN_RATE, CCN_INSERT_TIME) VALUES (:CCN_DATE, :CCN_CUR_FROM, :CCN_CUR_TO, :CCN_RATE, :CCN_INSERT_TIME) ",
       nativeQuery=true)
void insertExchanges​(@Param("CCN_DATE")
                     java.time.LocalDate date,
                     @Param("CCN_CUR_FROM")
                     int CCN_CUR_ID_FROM,
                     @Param("CCN_CUR_TO")
                     int CCN_CUR_ID_TO,
                     @Param("CCN_RATE")
                     float CCN_RATE,
                     @Param("CCN_INSERT_TIME")
                     java.time.LocalDateTime insertTime)
        This method is used to insert records in the currency_conversion table.
        Parameters:
        date - The date of the transaction. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD.
        CCN_CUR_ID_FROM - The ID of the currency that will be converted.
        CCN_CUR_ID_TO - The ID of the currency in which the CCN_CUR_ID_FROM will be converted.
        CCN_RATE - The conversion rate between specified currencies.
        insertTime - The date and time when the record was inserted.

      • updateRecord

@Query(value="UPDATE currency_conversion cur JOIN currency c ON c.CUR_ID = cur.CCN_CUR_ID_FROM JOIN currency c2 ON c2.CUR_ID = cur.CCN_CUR_ID_TO SET cur.CCN_RATE = ?1 WHERE c.CUR_ISO_CODE = ?3 AND c2.CUR_ISO_CODE = ?4 AND cur.CCN_DATE = ?2",
       nativeQuery=true)
void updateRecord​(float rate,
                  java.time.LocalDate date,
                  java.lang.String isoCodeFrom,
                  java.lang.String isoCodeTo)
        This method is used to update the rate of a specific record from the currency_conversion table.
        Parameters:
        rate - The updated conversion rate between specified currencies.
        date - The date of the transaction. Date format: YYYY-MM-DD.
        isoCodeFrom - The currency ISO to be converted (ex. USD, EUR, etc).
        isoCodeTo - The currency ISO to convert into (ex. USD, EUR, etc).
